@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "E_vaz_ive" where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed.

NOTE: As I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that E_vaz_ive runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga
      with a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any tile that is next to your position, which
is indicated by a coloured hexagonal shape. If both tiles are
connected by a coloured link, your position will move to that tile.
Note that you can also use the numbered keys of the numeric keypad
to move about on the game board, as shown below:

        7               9
    upper left     upper right

        4               6
      left            right

        1               3
    lower left     lower right

  As you leave a tile, a small hexagonal shape that is located on
that tile will change colour, if you return to that tile and leave
it again, the shape will change colour (as well as that of the
other tile), and so on, until it returns to its original colour and
the cycle starts again...

  To complete a game board, you have to go to the 'exit tile',
indicated by a 'pressed down' tile, which is located somewhere at
the lower position on the game board. Also, all the small hexagonal
shapes must be in either one of the 2 coulours shown on the shape
indicating your position... in other words, none of the shapes that
are on the tiles must be in black or white (or whatever colour you
use as colour 1 and 2 on your Workbench palette), and that includes
the shape that is on the exit tile.

  When you complete a game board, E_vaz_ive will display a new game
board to play with... try to make the fewest moves as you can for
each game board.

  Have fun!

OPTIONS

  You can change the colours of the links that connects the tiles
by clicking on the tile that indicates your position. This will
cycle between the colours that are used on the Workbench palette.

  You can restart the game any time by clicking on the 'Replay'
button.

  You can quit the game by clicking on the main window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

